HEADWORD: Stockjobber
<hw>Stock"job`ber</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Stock</ets> + <ets>job</ets>.]</ety> <def>One who speculates
in stocks for gain; one whose occupation is to buy and sell stocks. In
England a jobber acts as an intermediary between brokers.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stockjobbing</ent>⟦br⟧
